# Meeting-to-system integration

**Canon:** [`docs/SOP/MEETING_TO_SYSTEM_INTEGRATION_V1.md`](../../docs/SOP/MEETING_TO_SYSTEM_INTEGRATION_V1.md) · [`docs/SOP/CHATGPT_GITHUB_CODEX_CONTROL_PLANE_V1.md`](../../docs/SOP/CHATGPT_GITHUB_CODEX_CONTROL_PLANE_V1.md)

Every substantive founder thread is a working meeting. A useful conclusion is not organizationally complete until its durable outcome is integrated into GitHub.

## Default behavior

- Detect accepted decisions, changed assumptions, executable work, repeated pain, and organizational boundary failures during the conversation.
- Reconcile against current GitHub canon before writing.
- Update the smallest correct existing artifact; create a decision record, issue, charter, or PR only when needed.
- Integrate durable outcomes incrementally; do not depend solely on the founder saying `close out thread`.
- Structure implementation work for the Autobuilder with goal, canon, paths, constraints, acceptance criteria, evidence, and ownership.
- Update discovery links so future agents can find the result.
- Auto-ship completed docs/control-plane work per [`auto-ship.mdc`](auto-ship.mdc).
- Do not give the founder text to copy into GitHub when the repository is available.
- Do not ask the founder to choose file placement, branch mechanics, issue structure, technical decomposition, or reversible implementation defaults.
- Do not dump raw transcripts or record every exploratory thought as canon.

## Founder touchpoints

Ask only for:

- product truth or customer meaning that cannot be inferred safely;
- materially different product outcomes when canon conflicts;
- irreversible public, legal, financial, or external commitments;
- founder-only credentials, relationships, live validation, or private information;
- reversal of an accepted strategic decision.

When asking, present at most two outcome-level options and state the recommended default.

## Communication

For multi-step work: one concise opening update, one meaningful checkpoint, and one completion summary. Do not narrate every repository operation.

Default closing when integrated and unblocked:

> **Nothing required from you.**

If integration cannot be completed, name the exact missing capability or founder-only dependency. Do not claim a chat-only conclusion is durable.
